  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Rinse the<strong> brown rice</strong>, add it to a pot with plenty of<strong> cold water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p>\n<p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for 15-20 min or until it's tender with a slight bite</p>\n<p>Once cooked, drain and return it to the pot and keep covered until serving</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/pan-fried-fish-and-zingy-asian-ribbon-salad/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the rice is cooking, peel the <strong>carrot<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong>, then continue to peel lengths until you end up with a pile of carrot 'ribbons'</p>\n<p>Peel the<strong> cucumber</strong> into 'ribbons'</p>\n<p>Top, tail and slice the <strong>radishes </strong>as finely as you can</p>\n<p>Add the<strong> carrot ribbons</strong>,<strong> cucumber ribbons</strong> and <strong>sliced radishes</strong> to a large bowl – this is your <strong>salad</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/pan-fried-fish-and-zingy-asian-ribbon-salad/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Cut the red <strong>chilli<span class=\"text-danger\">[es]</span></strong> in half lengthways, deseed (scrape the seeds out with a teaspoon) and chop finely</p>\n<p>Cut the <strong>lime<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> in half</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/pan-fried-fish-and-zingy-asian-ribbon-salad/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Combine the <strong>soy sauce</strong>, <strong>toasted</strong> <strong>sesame oil</strong>, <strong>lime juice</strong> and <strong>chopped chilli</strong> with 1 tsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar</strong> in a small bowl – this is your <strong>Asian dressing</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/pan-fried-fish-and-zingy-asian-ribbon-salad/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Pat the <strong>basa fillets</strong> dry with kitchen paper and season lightly with<strong> salt</strong> on both sides</p>\n<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a high heat</p>\n<p>Once hot, add the <strong>basa fillets</strong> and cook for 2-3 min on each side or until cooked through and golden – this is your <strong>pan-fried fish</strong> </p>\n<p>Tip: Your fish is cooked when it turns opaque and flakes easily</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/pan-fried-fish-and-zingy-asian-ribbon-salad/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the basa fillets are cooking, chop the <strong>coriander</strong> roughly</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p> </p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/pan-fried-fish-and-zingy-asian-ribbon-salad/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>Asian dressing</strong> to the <strong>salad</strong> and give it a good mix up – this is your <strong>Asian salad </strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/pan-fried-fish-and-zingy-asian-ribbon-salad/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>pan-fried fish</strong> with the <strong>Asian salad</strong> and <strong>cooked</strong> <strong>brown rice</strong> to the side</p>\n<p>Drizzle any <strong>remaining dressing</strong> over the <strong>fish</strong> and <strong>rice</strong></p>\n<p>Garnish with the <strong>chopped coriander</strong> and <strong>roasted peanuts</strong></p>\n<p>Enjoy! </p>",
      "order": 8
    }
  ],
